## FAQ

### What are Dodola and Perperuna rituals?
Dodola (Serbia) and Perperuna (Bulgaria) are traditional rainmaking processions where a young girl covered in leaves and greenery leads the community while singing and water is poured over her to invoke rain.

### Were these rituals performed throughout the Balkans?
Yes, they were recorded in Serbia, Bulgaria, North Macedonia, and Romania, particularly in agricultural villages facing drought.

