The girl represented fertility and vegetation. Covering her in greenery symbolically connected her to crops and nature.

### Did these rituals include chants or songs?
Yes, communities sang specific rain-invoking chants as the girl processed through the village, often rhythmically and repeatedly to reinforce the magic.

### Are these rituals connected to modern witchcraft?
No, these are traditional folk survival practices, not modern spiritual systems. They are based on agricultural needs and sympathetic magic.
